events.1: Konjikala, the ancient settlement, leveled by an earthquake in the 1st century BC and rebuilt, flourished until its destruction by Mongols in the 13th century
events.1830: Ahal branch of the Teke tribe arrives in the area and establishes several semi-nomadic villages (auls) including Askhabad
events.1881: City officially founded as a fortified garrison and named Askhabad
events.1882: Wagon road built through the mountains to Quchan, Iran, leading to increased trade and settlement
events.1897: Population reaches 19,428, with one third being Persian
events.1908: First Bahá'í House of Worship built in Askhabad
events.1924: Turkmen SSR established with Poltoratsk as its capital
events.1927: Original name, Ashkhabad, restored but in the form of Ashgabat
events.1948: Major earthquake strikes Ashgabat, killing a significant portion of the population
events.2003: Street names in Ashgabat replaced by serial numbers
events.2013: Ashgabat included in Guinness Book of Records for possessing the world's highest concentration of white marble buildings
events.2018: Government announces plans for extensive urban renewal and residential construction projects
events.2022: Government announces plans to demolish one- and two-story houses in several microdistricts of central Ashgabat and replace them with modern apartment buildings
